        "created_at": "2019-02-05T01:38:23.057Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That all sounds right. You could certainly follow the same approach as the in-tree bindings, offering releases at different versions with the latest API header version used as of that release. In fact, this is what we did historically with the Go bindings when they were maintained in a separate repository.</p>\n<p>I\u2019ll have to defer to the maintainers of the other bindings to provide their experiences with the other approaches.</p>",
